news.title: Sintex plans five per cent market share in pipes & fitting segment
news.para: So, water storage tanks contribute about 60-65 per cent of overall revenue. Sintex has always been a premium brand. We have recently launched more economical products in the water storage tanks segment and expect a big jump in the overall revenue.

news.title: JSW One Platforms raises ₹340 crore at a valuation of $1 billion
news.para: Gaurav Sachdeva, joint managing director & CEO of JSW One Platforms said, "This capital allows us to strengthen national supply chain leadership in steel and cement categories, deepen distribution and logistics networks across India."

news.title: ILP 4 India 1 acquires 3.95 acres land parcel in Mumbai for ₹193.5 crore
news.para: The transaction also includes multiple existing buildings on the acquired land parcel with a total built-up area of ~4,519 sq. m (~48,641 sq. ft), according to the IGR documents reviewed by Square Yards.

news.title: Odisha government appoints interim chairperson for RERA
news.para: ​The govt move comes two days after the third and only member of ORERA retired, making the authority virtually defunct. The chairperson, Siddhanta Das, exited the office in Feb, while the chairperson (in-charge), Gopal Chandra Patnaik, retired on Saturday.

news.title: Ghaziabad board to meet next week to discuss master plan, land rates for new township
news.para: In March, a six-member committee announced compensation at four times the existing circle rates for farmers in Mathurapur, Shamsher, Champatnagar, Bhanera-Khurd and Nangla Feroze Mohan Nagar, whose land is to be acquired for the township.

news.title: Rajasthan's housing minister launches three residential projects in Jaipur, five in other cities
news.para: ​JDA officials said the Ganga Vihar Housing Scheme, situated near Bassi railway station, will feature 233 plots priced at Rs 14,000 per sqm as the reserve rate.

news.title: Liquidator puts Jet Airways' office space in Mumbai's BKC on the block
news.para: The liquidator has set a reserve price of Rs 335.24 crore for the property to be auctioned next month under the Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code, 2016.

news.title: Over 8,000 flat registries in nine Greater Noida projects stuck over ₹400 crore dues
news.para: While land parcels for the projects were allotted between 2007 and 2011 when Greater Noida offered a 2.75 FAR, developers redrew maps and got them vetted by UPSIDA again after FAR was increased to 3.5 in 2013.

news.title: Lens on commercial buildings in New Town, Kolkata
news.para: Officials said there are close to 1,200 buildings across New Town which are violating the commercial-use rule in some way or other.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Fraudulent real estate ads on social media worry property buyers as experts raise concern
news.para: The fraudulent schemes typically operate through two approaches: direct contact through provided phone numbers or systematic collection of buyers' personal information.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Over 2,400 flats under RERA rehabilitation clause yet to be completed
news.para: But over the years, none of the 2,491 flats in Antriksh Sanskriti, La Casa Ansal Aquapolis, Utopia Estate, ASG Apple 7 and Spring View Heights along national highway 9 and Vasundhara Grand in Atal Chowk have been handed over.

news.title: MREAT quashes MahaRERA's order over arbitration in Winter Green project
news.para: The allottees, represented by advocates Anil D'Souza and Rupali P in MREAT, booked flats in Winter Green, part of Rivali Park project, and paid substantial sums.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government drafts building construction byelaws
news.para: The housing and urban planning department presented the draft to Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath for approval, aiming to streamline and make construction and business operations more accessible, it said.

news.title: EOW arrests Unnati Fortune Holding's director for siphoning off crores from private bank
news.para: The private bank had sanctioned loans of Rs 100 crore and Rs 65 crore in 2016 and 2017 for the construction of projects in Noida and Gurgaon by M/s Unnati Fortune Holding Limited (UFHL).

news.title: VVIP Group to invest ₹800 crore in new housing project in Greater Noida
news.para: "With an investment of approximately Rs 800 crore, the project will comprise 350-plus premium residential units in a single-phase development," it said.

news.title: SGRE Fund invests ₹125 crore in two housing projects in NCR
news.para: The fund, launched by promoters of Nirala World and Sea Fund, will provide finance to those real estate companies which are struggling to get funds for the revival of the projects and their completion.

news.title: The Anatomy of Better real estate: Inside the Making of K Better Homes
news.para: Across Pune’s prime residential markets: K Town (Kiwale), K Ville (Kiwale), K Shire (Punawale), K City (Keshavnagar), and K Pune (Bavdhan). K Better Homes has designed spaces that challenge conventions.

news.title: Macrotech Developers 'seriously' looking for land to enter Delhi-NCR
news.para: ​Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, which sells properties under the 'Lodha brand', is one of the leading real estate firms in the country. At present, the company has a presence in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), Pune and Bengaluru.

news.title: Commercial property prices in Germany rise 2.3% in Q1 2025
news.para: The increase was bigger than the 0.5% gain in the fourth quarter of last year, which was the first quarterly increase since early 2022 as the country's real estate sector grappled with its worst crisis in decades.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body urges property owners to complete KYC
news.para: NMMC spokesperson Mahendra Konde said the move will enable residents to conveniently view and pay their property tax bills via mobile phones, receive critical updates such as water supply alerts, heavy rainfall warnings, emergency notifications, and traffic advisories directly on their devices.
